all chocolate glazed.

12:16.070 --> 12:17.780
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

12:24.161 --> 12:26.497
[Sighs]

12:28.249 --> 12:29.875
You get your dad on board?

12:31.335 --> 12:32.461
Mm-hmm.

12:34.755 --> 12:36.840
I want to adopt Wayne.

12:36.966 --> 12:38.175
Like, officially.

12:38.300 --> 12:39.969
If something happens to you,

12:40.094 --> 12:43.764
if you disappear again,
I could lose him.

12:43.889 --> 12:46.058
And I can't lose my son.

12:47.434 --> 12:48.727
Yeah. Of course.

12:48.852 --> 12:50.354
He needs you.

12:54.608 --> 12:56.402
[Clears throat]
He needs his mother, too.

12:56.527 --> 12:57.820
[ Sniffles ]

12:59.363 --> 13:00.823
He needs stability.

13:02.199 --> 13:06.203
The past few days, you set
the freakin' house on fire,

13:06.328 --> 13:08.372
disappeared in the middle
of the night,

13:08.497 --> 13:10.916
and went on a suicide mission
to try to take on Charlie Manx.

13:13.210 --> 13:15.045
- I know.
- Yeah. Do you?

13:15.170 --> 13:18.299
I get it.
A lot of bad shit has happened.

13:18.424 --> 13:21.885
You're not the only one on team
McCarmody who's traumatized.

13:22.011 --> 13:24.847
You are the only one
who uses it as an excuse

13:24.972 --> 13:26.682
to not deal
with your problems...

13:26.807 --> 13:30.894
and to also not be, like,
present.

13:33.063 --> 13:34.815
Look, I want this to work.

13:38.110 --> 13:40.070
But if you don't figure
your stuff out...

13:42.489 --> 13:43.699
I don't know.

13:58.547 --> 13:59.715
[ Telephone ringing,
indistinct conversations]

13:59.840 --> 14:00.966
TABITHA:
I cross-checked the alias

14:01.091 --> 14:02.384
Bing Partridge
gave to Lou Carmody

14:02.509 --> 14:04.636
with businesses
that deal in Sevoflurane.

14:04.762 --> 14:07.264
I found three places in Maine
with gas on site

14:07.389 --> 14:09.391
who employ someone named
Ethan Andersen.

14:09.516 --> 14:10.893
One of them could be Bing.

14:11.894 --> 14:13.687
CHITRA: The attack
happened in Colorado.

14:13.812 --> 14:16.440
What makes you think the suspect
would come back east?

14:16.565 --> 14:17.441
TABITHA:
The Maine ID.

14:17.566 --> 14:19.443
Bing lived under the radar
for eight years.

14:19.568 --> 14:21.195
Why not regroup
at a trusted hideout,

14:21.320 --> 14:23.739
especially one that provides
access to gas?

14:23.864 --> 14:26.992
If I can get one of
those businesses to ID him,

14:27.117 --> 14:29.828
give rne a home address,
we can sit on the place,

14:29.953 --> 14:32.498
move on him
before he hurts anyone else.

14:35.751 --> 14:37.753
Women like you and I
are few and far between

14:37.878 --> 14:39.338
in this field office.

14:40.672 --> 14:43.300
Daltry and his boys club
is always looking for reasons

14:43.425 --> 14:45.302
to make that number smaller.

14:45.427 --> 14:47.471
The last time you walked in here
talking about Bing,

14:47.596 --> 14:50.933
you broke protocol and shared
confidential information

14:51.058 --> 14:51.934
with your girlfriend --

14:52.059 --> 14:53.936
My head's on straight.

14:54.061 --> 14:55.437
CHITRA:
You're a bright star, Tabs.

14:55.562 --> 14:57.189
I can't afford to lose you.

14:57.314 --> 14:58.941
TABITHA: We can't afford
to lose Partridge.

14:59.858 --> 15:02.152
I'll be smart.

15:02.277 --> 15:03.654
I promise.

15:05.531 --> 15:06.907
I don't wanna hurt him.

15:07.032 --> 15:08.534
LOU: Here, we'll --
we'll do it quick, you know?

15:08.659 --> 15:10.285
You just --

15:10.411 --> 15:13.831
just hook him on,
and he won't feel a thing.

15:13.956 --> 15:15.165
Here.
You want me to do it?

15:15.290 --> 15:17.167
- WAYNE: Yeah.
- Okay. Here. Pass it.

15:17.292 --> 15:18.168
Uh...

15:18.293 --> 15:20.504
Hoo. Okay.

15:20.629 --> 15:23.674
Here we go.
Let's get it right in there.

15:25.259 --> 15:26.635
Ugh.

15:30.139 --> 15:31.265
[ Lure rattles ]

15:33.267 --> 15:36.061
CHRIS:
Bass like these better.

15:36.186 --> 15:37.771
LOU:
[Chuckling ] Alright.

15:37.896 --> 15:39.022
Thanks.

15:39.148 --> 15:41.358
Put it in like that.

15:41.483 --> 15:44.987
Alright, lil man,
let's get you fishing.

15:54.538 --> 15:56.623
You okay?

16:02.504 --> 16:04.131
I don't know how to do that.

16:06.049 --> 16:07.342
Be normal.

16:07.468 --> 16:11.430
Well, news flash -- none
of those dudes are normal.

16:11.555 --> 16:14.475
Lou dresses like a storm trooper
for fun.

16:14.600 --> 16:16.018
[ Chuckles ]

16:16.143 --> 16:18.687
And Wayne, he's cooler
than all of us combined.

16:18.812 --> 16:21.273
And your dad's gone
all Bear Grylls

16:21.398 --> 16:23.317
in a spooky horror cabin.

16:26.195 --> 16:28.614
But they don't have a Bridge.

16:28.739 --> 16:30.365
Neither did you for eight years.

16:30.491 --> 16:31.408
That doesn't matter.

16:31.533 --> 16:33.452
My head was always
someplace else.

16:36.079 --> 16:37.539
For a long time,

16:37.664 --> 16:40.709
the Tiles were the only
consistent thing in my life.

16:41.835 --> 16:45.130
So wherever I went,
whoever I lost,

16:45.255 --> 16:46.757
the Tiles were there.

16:52.846 --> 16:54.389
And then I fell in love.

16:58.268 --> 17:01.021
I always thought it was just
gonna be me and my Tiles.

17:01.146 --> 17:05.233
But Tabitha's my home
'cause I chose her.

17:09.863 --> 17:11.365
Did you, though?

17:13.659 --> 17:15.953
You're here with your Tiles.

17:17.287 --> 17:18.454
WAYNE:
I caught a fish!

17:18.579 --> 17:20.457
-[Loulaughs]
- CHRIS: Alright. Alright.

17:20.582 --> 17:24.211
Yeah, well,
nobody said it was easy.

17:27.047 --> 17:28.924
CHRIS: A little bit of slack.
A little bit of slack.

17:30.842 --> 17:32.970
[Humming]

17:37.933 --> 17:40.185
Well, Wayne had fun today.

17:40.310 --> 17:42.437
[ Chuckles]
Yeah. Me too.

17:46.233 --> 17:47.818
- Here.
- Can I -- Yeah.

17:49.194 --> 17:51.697
- There?
- Yep. Right there.

17:54.783 --> 17:55.951
Alright, you hold it in.

17:56.076 --> 17:58.370
- Let's put it down.
- Okay.

18:00.998 --> 18:02.457
Eight years.

18:02.583 --> 18:04.793
The first thing we do together
is build a bomb.

18:04.918 --> 18:06.878
[ Both chuckle]

18:07.879 --> 18:09.590
Well, there is nothing
more Haverhill

18:09.715 --> 18:11.341
than blowing shit up
in your yard.

18:11.466 --> 18:14.052
CHRIS: [Laughs]
Yeah. You're right.

18:14.177 --> 18:15.971
Except these'll
jelly the insides

18:16.096 --> 18:17.764
of anybody within 100 feet.

18:19.808 --> 18:21.351
Good.

18:31.486 --> 18:33.780
My hands shook for like a week.

18:41.246 --> 18:43.790
When did you stop
wanting a drink?

18:43.915 --> 18:45.542
[Sighs]

18:52.591 --> 18:54.009
[Sighs]

18:54.134 --> 18:55.802
[ Floorboards creaking ]

19:04.519 --> 19:06.688
Whoa.

19:06.813 --> 19:08.106
L-l -- I woke up.

19:08.231 --> 19:09.399
Wayne wasn't there. I --

19:09.524 --> 19:11.026
I found him out here.

19:14.071 --> 19:16.740
VIC: Wayne, baby.

19:16.865 --> 19:18.116
Hey.

19:18.241 --> 19:20.035
[Whispering ] Sometimes
Mom doesn't like us.

19:23.914 --> 19:26.124
I'll, uh...

19:26.249 --> 19:28.043
I'll do it.

19:28.168 --> 19:29.586
VIC: Yeah.

19:29.711 --> 19:31.129
LOU: Yeah, we're just gonna
go back to bed.

19:31.254 --> 19:32.297
Come on.

19:33.965 --> 19:35.801
[ Door closes ]

19:39.221 --> 19:40.931
- CHRIS: Come on, Vic --
- Don't.

19:41.640 --> 19:43.183
Don't.

19:56.363 --> 19:58.990
TABITHA: He goes by the name
Ethan Andersen.

19:59.116 --> 20:00.450
DENTIST: Yeah.
He's a janitor here.

20:00.575 --> 20:02.619
A real oddball.
Disappeared last week.

20:02.744 --> 20:05.038
Do you guys have
a home address on file?

20:05.163 --> 20:06.790
